node.text: I posted these last night in my stories and I wanted to save them to a highlight but they had disappeared before I could do that so I compiled it here. These were done before Rachael Kirkconnell made her statement. I would like to echo @brettsvergara ‘s sentiment that this is not my apology to accept or judge. @therachlindsay and @taymocha have been shouldering this work in the Bachelor franchise. Rachel spoke into this on Higher Learning. Taylor did an IG live with @theblckchelorettes that I encourage you to watch and open yourselves too. @chattybroads go into on their latest episode as well. I am not perfect, I don’t have the right words, I am not free of learned bias. I have a long way to go but I see and empathize with my friends and BIPOC cast mates. If you are learning from Black women, pay black women.

Each set is made from 25 plastic bottles, saves 3 gallons of water, creates 75% less CO2 emissions and arrives in 💯 compostable packaging! Make every day earth day. 
P.S. This video walks you through using codes (like FIGSxMaltby) to save money on the app 🤍💚💙 Sign in, fill out shipping and then add your code! Voila! Save money and help the planet. You can also join the waitlist for the mask FIGS is launching 🙌🏽

node.text:
I’m not eloquent, I’m angry. I’m angry that the CDC, JCAHO, and OSHA rules and regulations are being thrown out the window when it comes to protecting the people who are protecting YOU. I’m angry that there are not enough masks and personal protective equipment (PPE) to protect my friends and family in hospitals throughout the country. Its BULLSHIT! The Doctors, Nurses, RT’s, CNA’s, PA’s, NP’s, security, cooking and janitorial staff are all putting their lives at risk to protect and serve us and they are being told to reuse masks and PPE. Some people have had the same masks for over a week. A week! N95 masks are single use. Your health care staff are now making up 20% of those infected and in critical care in hospitals and your health care staff are among those dying from COVID19. 
Social distancing is not going to a new friends house every day, social distancing is not having a bunch of people over at your house. This virus spreads and will continue to infect people. We are being asked to stay home to protect each other. Our grandparents and parents went to war. Please think about this when you go to your friends houses. I know its an inconvenience, I know it sucks, but make use of apps like FaceTime and Houseparty. You can still play games with your friends and interact with people. We are all in this together but I am BEGGING you to think about the health of the people taking care of everyone sick. They are getting sick, they are self distancing in their own homes from their partners and from their kids to keep them safe and too many are dying in an effort to protect you.

node.text: My angel friend  @leahblevinsmusic just released her first full length album ‘First Time Feeling’ and it’s perfect. I am a very proud friend and have zero bias in telling you this is a damn beautiful album and you should go to leahblevins.com and buy it. This was also the first show I was able to see (masked) back @thebasementeast after the tornado tried to destroy it. The Beast is back and royally supporting Nashville through the pandemic. #newmusic #leahblevinsmusic #trendingmusic #americana #nashvilleamericana #thebasement #thebasementeast #supportlivemusic

node.text:
I’ve never been someone who could work out every day. I like to enjoy movement and I always feel better when I do. I don’t work out to punish myself for my sweet tooth. I like to move in ways that make me feel good and happy. I made a commitment to myself a couple weeks ago to move every day for at least 15 minutes. Now, 15 minutes is 15 minutes. It doesn’t seem like much- I usually spend at least that scrolling on my phone when I get up in the morning, even on early OR days. But it just feels good. Some days it looks like a little yoga flow, sometimes it’s a treadmill, a hike, or pilates @melioramovement or a kitchen dance party/ shake it out. This week it’s looked like daily walks with my momma. ♥️

And those wanting some @wearfigs but think they only make scrubs… yall- their performance bra’s and leggings are next level. Fit, support, movement- ✔️✅✔️ Helping me stay healthy for the long haul and comfy on the couch 🙃😂 #wearfigs #listentoyourbody #healthymovement

node.text: Just an ex- night shift nurse, happy at 0630 heading INTO work 😃 Literally never thought I would leave night shift let alone the NICU, but it feels really wild waking up happy to head into work 😅.
